pokemon.name: Bulbasaur
pokemon.blurb:
A strange seed was
planted on its
back at birth. The plant sprouts
and grows with
this POKÃ©MON.

pokemon.name: Ivysaur
pokemon.blurb:
When the bulb on
its back grows
large, it appears to lose the
ability to stand
on its hind legs.

pokemon.name: Venusaur
pokemon.blurb:
The plant blooms
when it is
absorbing solar energy. It stays
on the move to
seek sunlight.

pokemon.name: Charmander
pokemon.blurb:
Obviously prefers
hot places. When
it rains, steam is said to spout
from the tip of
its tail.

pokemon.name: Charmeleon
pokemon.blurb:
When it swings
its burning tail,
it elevates the temperature to
unbearably high
levels.

pokemon.name: Charizard
pokemon.blurb:
Spits fire that
is hot enough to
melt boulders. Known to cause
forest fires
unintentionally.

pokemon.name: Squirtle
pokemon.blurb:
After birth, its
back swells and
hardens into a shell. Powerfully
sprays foam from
its mouth.

pokemon.name: Wartortle
pokemon.blurb:
Often hides in
water to stalk
unwary prey. For swimming fast, it
moves its ears to
maintain balance.

pokemon.name: Blastoise
pokemon.blurb:
A brutal POKÃ©MON
with pressurized
water jets on its shell. They are
used for high
speed tackles.

pokemon.name: Caterpie
pokemon.blurb:
Its short feet are tipped with suction
pads that enable it to tirelessly climb
slopes and walls.

pokemon.name: Metapod
pokemon.blurb:
This POKÃ©MON is
vulnerable to
attack while its shell is soft,
exposing its weak
and tender body.

pokemon.name: Butterfree
pokemon.blurb:
In battle, it
flaps its wings
at high speed to release highly
toxic dust into
the air.

pokemon.name: Weedle
pokemon.blurb:
Often found in
forests, eating
leaves. It has a sharp
venomous stinger
on its head.

pokemon.name: Kakuna
pokemon.blurb:
Almost incapable
of moving, this
POKÃ©MON can only harden its shell
to protect itself
from predators.

pokemon.name: Beedrill
pokemon.blurb:
It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and
its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

pokemon.name: Pidgey
pokemon.blurb:
A common sight in
forests and woods.
It flaps its wings at ground
level to kick up
blinding sand.

pokemon.name: Pidgeotto
pokemon.blurb:
Very protective
of its sprawling
territorial area, this POKÃ©MON will
fiercely peck at
any intruder.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot
pokemon.blurb:
When hunting, it
skims the surface
of water at high speed to pick off
unwary prey such
as MAGIKARP.

pokemon.name: Rattata
pokemon.blurb:
Bites anything
when it attacks.
Small and very quick, it is a
common sight in
many places.

pokemon.name: Raticate
pokemon.blurb:
It uses its whisÂ­
kers to maintain
its balance. It apparently
slows down if
they are cut off.

pokemon.name: Spearow
pokemon.blurb:
It flaps its small wings busily to
fly. Using its beak, it searches
in grass for prey.

pokemon.name: Fearow
pokemon.blurb:
With its huge and
magnificent wings,
it can keep aloft without ever
having to land
for rest.

pokemon.name: Ekans
pokemon.blurb:
Moves silently
and stealthily.
Eats the eggs of birds, such as
PIDGEY and
SPEAROW, whole.

pokemon.name: Arbok
pokemon.blurb:
It is rumored that
the ferocious
warning markings on its belly
differ from area
to area.

pokemon.name: Pikachu
pokemon.blurb:
When several of
these POKÃ©MON
gather, their electricity could
build and cause
lightning storms.

pokemon.name: Raichu
pokemon.blurb:
Its long tail
serves as a
ground to protect itself from its
own high voltage
power.

pokemon.name: Sandshrew
pokemon.blurb:
Burrows deep
underground in
arid locations far from water.
It only emerges
to hunt for food.

pokemon.name: Sandslash
pokemon.blurb:
Curls up into a
spiny ball when
threatened. It can roll while
curled up to
attack or escape.

pokemon.name: Nidoran-f
pokemon.blurb:
Although small,
its venomous
barbs render this POKÃ©MON dangerous.
The female has
smaller horns.

pokemon.name: Nidorina
pokemon.blurb:
The female's horn
develops slowly.
Prefers physical attacks such as
clawing and
biting.

pokemon.name: Nidoqueen
pokemon.blurb:
Its hard scales
provide strong
protection. It uses its hefty
bulk to execute
powerful moves.

pokemon.name: Nidoran-m
pokemon.blurb:
Stiffens its ears
to sense danger.
The larger its horns, the more
powerful its
secreted venom.

pokemon.name: Nidorino
pokemon.blurb:
An aggressive
POKÃ©MON that is
quick to attack. The horn on its
head secretes a
powerful venom.

pokemon.name: Nidoking
pokemon.blurb:
It uses its
powerful tail in
battle to smash, constrict, then
break the prey's
bones.

pokemon.name: Clefairy
pokemon.blurb:
Its magical and
cute appeal has
many admirers. It is rare and
found only in
certain areas.

pokemon.name: Clefable
pokemon.blurb:
A timid fairy
POKÃ©MON that is
rarely seen. It will run and hide
the moment it
senses people.

pokemon.name: Vulpix
pokemon.blurb:
At the time of
birth, it has
just one tail. The tail splits
from its tip as
it grows older.

pokemon.name: Ninetales
pokemon.blurb:
Very smart and
very vengeful.
Grabbing one of its many tails
could result in a
1000-year curse.

pokemon.name: Jigglypuff
pokemon.blurb:
When its huge eyes
light up, it sings
a mysteriously soothing melody
that lulls its
enemies to sleep.

pokemon.name: Wigglytuff
pokemon.blurb:
The body is soft
and rubbery. When
angered, it will suck in air and
inflate itself to
an enormous size.

pokemon.name: Zubat
pokemon.blurb:
Forms colonies in
perpetually dark
places. Uses ultrasonic waves
to identify and
approach targets.

pokemon.name: Golbat
pokemon.blurb:
Once it strikes,
it will not stop
draining energy from the victim
even if it gets
too heavy to fly.

pokemon.name: Oddish
pokemon.blurb:
During the day, it
stays in the cold
underground to avoid the sun.
It grows by bathÂ­
ing in moonlight.

pokemon.name: Gloom
pokemon.blurb:
What appears to be
drool is actually
sweet honey. It is very sticky and
clings stubbornly
if touched.

pokemon.name: Vileplume
pokemon.blurb:
The larger its
petals, the more
toxic pollen it contains. Its big
head is heavy and
hard to hold up.

pokemon.name: Paras
pokemon.blurb:
Burrows to suck
tree roots. The
mushrooms on its back grow by drawÂ­
ing nutrients from
the bug host.

pokemon.name: Parasect
pokemon.blurb:
A host-parasite
pair in which the
parasite mushroom has taken over the
host bug. Prefers
damp places.

pokemon.name: Venonat
pokemon.blurb:
Lives in the
shadows of tall
trees where it eats insects. It
is attracted by
light at night.

pokemon.name: Venomoth
pokemon.blurb:
The dust-like
scales covering
its wings are color coded to
indicate the kinds
of poison it has.

pokemon.name: Diglett
pokemon.blurb:
Lives about one
yard underground
where it feeds on plant roots. It
sometimes appears
above ground.

pokemon.name: Dugtrio
pokemon.blurb:
A team of DIGLETT
triplets.
It triggers huge earthquakes by
burrowing 60 miles
underground.

pokemon.name: Meowth
pokemon.blurb:
Adores circular
objects. Wanders
the streets on a nightly basis to
look for dropped
loose change.

pokemon.name: Persian
pokemon.blurb:
Although its fur
has many admirers,
it is tough to raise as a pet
because of its
fickle meanness.

pokemon.name: Psyduck
pokemon.blurb:
While lulling its
enemies with its
vacant look, this wily POKÃ©MON will
use psychokinetic
powers.

pokemon.name: Golduck
pokemon.blurb:
Often seen swimÂ­
ming elegantly by
lake shores. It is often mistaken
for the Japanese
monster, Kappa.

pokemon.name: Mankey
pokemon.blurb:
Extremely quick to
anger. It could
be docile one moment then
thrashing away
the next instant.

pokemon.name: Primeape
pokemon.blurb:
Always furious
and tenacious to
boot. It will not abandon chasing
its quarry until
it is caught.

pokemon.name: Growlithe
pokemon.blurb:
Very protective
of its territory.
It will bark and bite to repel
intruders from
its space.

pokemon.name: Arcanine
pokemon.blurb:
A POKÃ©MON that
has been admired
since the past for its beauty.
It runs agilely
as if on wings.

pokemon.name: Poliwag
pokemon.blurb:
Its newly grown
legs prevent it
from running. It appears to prefer
swimming than
trying to stand.

pokemon.name: Poliwhirl
pokemon.blurb:
Capable of living
in or out of
water. When out of water, it
sweats to keep
its body slimy.

pokemon.name: Poliwrath
pokemon.blurb:
An adept swimmer
at both the front
crawl and breast stroke. Easily
overtakes the best
human swimmers.

pokemon.name: Abra
pokemon.blurb:
Using its ability
to read minds, it
will identify impending danger
and TELEPORT to
safety.

pokemon.name: Kadabra
pokemon.blurb:
It emits special
alpha waves from
its body that induce headaches
just by being
close by.

pokemon.name: Alakazam
pokemon.blurb:
Its brain can outÂ­
perform a superÂ­
computer. Its intelligence
quotient is said
to be 5,000.

pokemon.name: Machop
pokemon.blurb:
Loves to build
its muscles.
It trains in all styles of martial
arts to become
even stronger.

pokemon.name: Machoke
pokemon.blurb:
Its muscular body
is so powerful, it
must wear a power save belt to be
able to regulate
its motions.

pokemon.name: Machamp
pokemon.blurb:
Using its heavy
muscles, it throws
powerful punches that can send the
victim clear over
the horizon.

pokemon.name: Bellsprout
pokemon.blurb:
It prefers hot and humid
environments. It is quick at
capturing prey with its vines.

pokemon.name: Weepinbell
pokemon.blurb:
It spits out
POISONPOWDER to
immobilize the enemy and then
finishes it with
a spray of ACID.

pokemon.name: Victreebel
pokemon.blurb:
Said to live in
huge colonies
deep in jungles, although no one
has ever returned
from there.

pokemon.name: Tentacool
pokemon.blurb:
Drifts in shallow
seas. Anglers who
hook them by accident are
often punished by
its stinging acid.

pokemon.name: Tentacruel
pokemon.blurb:
The tentacles are
normally kept
short. On hunts, they are extended
to ensnare and
immobilize prey.

pokemon.name: Geodude
pokemon.blurb:
Found in fields
and mountains.
Mistaking them for boulders,
people often step
or trip on them.

pokemon.name: Graveler
pokemon.blurb:
Rolls down slopes
to move. It rolls
over any obstacle without slowing
or changing its
direction.

pokemon.name: Golem
pokemon.blurb:
Its boulder-like
body is extremely
hard. It can easily withstand
dynamite blasts
without damage.

pokemon.name: Ponyta
pokemon.blurb:
As a newborn, it can barely stand.
However, through galloping, its
legs are made tougher and faster.

pokemon.name: Rapidash
pokemon.blurb:
Very competitive,
this POKÃ©MON will
chase anything that moves fast
in the hopes of
racing it.

pokemon.name: Slowpoke
pokemon.blurb:
Incredibly slow
and dopey. It
takes 5 seconds for it to feel
pain when under
attack.

pokemon.name: Slowbro
pokemon.blurb:
The SHELLDER that
is latched onto
SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed
on the host's left
over scraps.

pokemon.name: Magnemite
pokemon.blurb:
Uses anti-gravity
to stay suspended.
Appears without warning and uses
THUNDER WAVE and
similar moves.

pokemon.name: Magneton
pokemon.blurb:
Formed by several
MAGNEMITEs linked
together. They frequently appear
when sunspots
flare up.

pokemon.name: Farfetchd
pokemon.blurb:
The sprig of
green onions it
holds is its weapon. It is
used much like a
metal sword.

pokemon.name: Doduo
pokemon.blurb:
A bird that makes
up for its poor
flying with its fast foot speed.
Leaves giant
footprints.

pokemon.name: Dodrio
pokemon.blurb:
Uses its three
brains to execute
complex plans. While two heads
sleep, one head
stays awake.

pokemon.name: Seel
pokemon.blurb:
The protruding
horn on its head
is very hard. It is used for
bashing through
thick ice.

pokemon.name: Dewgong
pokemon.blurb:
Stores thermal
energy in its
body. Swims at a steady 8 knots
even in intensely
cold waters.

pokemon.name: Grimer
pokemon.blurb:
Appears in filthy
areas. Thrives by
sucking up polluted sludge
that is pumped
out of factories.

pokemon.name: Muk
pokemon.blurb:
Thickly covered
with a filthy,
vile sludge. It is so toxic, even
its footprints
contain poison.

pokemon.name: Shellder
pokemon.blurb:
Its hard shell
repels any kind
of attack. It is vulnerable
only when its
shell is open.

pokemon.name: Cloyster
pokemon.blurb:
When attacked, it
launches its
horns in quick volleys. Its
innards have
never been seen.

pokemon.name: Gastly
pokemon.blurb:
Almost invisible,
this gaseous
POKÃ©MON cloaks the target and
puts it to sleep
without notice.

pokemon.name: Haunter
pokemon.blurb:
Because of its
ability to slip
through block walls, it is said
to be from anÂ­
other dimension.

pokemon.name: Gengar
pokemon.blurb:
Under a full moon,
this POKÃ©MON
likes to mimic the shadows of
people and laugh
at their fright.

pokemon.name: Onix
pokemon.blurb:
Opening its large mouth, it ingests
massive amounts of soil and creates
long tunnels.

pokemon.name: Drowzee
pokemon.blurb:
Puts enemies to
sleep then eats
their dreams. Occasionally gets
sick from eating
bad dreams.

pokemon.name: Hypno
pokemon.blurb:
When it locks eyes
with an enemy, it
will use a mix of PSI moves such as
HYPNOSIS and
CONFUSION.

pokemon.name: Krabby
pokemon.blurb:
Its pincers are
not only powerful
weapons, they are used for balance
when walking
sideways.

pokemon.name: Kingler
pokemon.blurb:
The large pincer
has 10000 hp of
crushing power. However, its huge
size makes it
unwieldy to use.

pokemon.name: Voltorb
pokemon.blurb:
Usually found in
power plants.
Easily mistaken for a POKÃ© BALL,
they have zapped
many people.

pokemon.name: Electrode
pokemon.blurb:
It stores electric
energy under very
high pressure. It often explodes
with little or no
provocation.

pokemon.name: Exeggcute
pokemon.blurb:
Using telepathy only they can
employ, they always form a
cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.

pokemon.name: Exeggutor
pokemon.blurb:
Legend has it that
on rare occasions,
one of its heads will drop off and
continue on as an
EXEGGCUTE.

pokemon.name: Cubone
pokemon.blurb:
Because it never
removes its skull
helmet, no one has ever seen
this POKÃ©MON's
real face.

pokemon.name: Marowak
pokemon.blurb:
The bone it holds
is its key weapon.
It throws the bone skillfully
like a boomerang
to KO targets.

pokemon.name: Hitmonlee
pokemon.blurb:
When in a hurry,
its legs lengthen
progressively. It runs smoothly
with extra long,
loping strides.

pokemon.name: Hitmonchan
pokemon.blurb:
While apparently
doing nothing, it
fires punches in lightning fast
volleys that are
impossible to see.

pokemon.name: Lickitung
pokemon.blurb:
Its tongue can be
extended like a
chameleon's. It leaves a tingling
sensation when it
licks enemies.

pokemon.name: Koffing
pokemon.blurb:
If one gets close
enough to it when
it expels poisonÂ­ ous gas, the gas
swirling inside it
can be seen.

pokemon.name: Weezing
pokemon.blurb:
If one of the twin
KOFFING inflates,
the other one deflates. It conÂ­
stantly mixes its
poisonous gases.

pokemon.name: Rhyhorn
pokemon.blurb:
A POKÃ©MON with a
one-track mind.
Once it charges,  it won't stop
running until it
falls asleep.

pokemon.name: Rhydon
pokemon.blurb:
Protected by an
armor-like hide,
it is capable of living in molten
lava of 3,600
degrees.

pokemon.name: Chansey
pokemon.blurb:
A rare and elusive
POKÃ©MON that is
said to bring happiness to those
who manage to get
it.

pokemon.name: Tangela
pokemon.blurb:
The whole body is
swathed with wide
vines that are similar to seaÂ­
weed. Its vines
shake as it walks.

pokemon.name: Kangaskhan
pokemon.blurb:
The infant rarely
ventures out of
its mother's protective pouch
until it is 3
years old.

pokemon.name: Horsea
pokemon.blurb:
Known to shoot
down flying bugs
with precision blasts of ink
from the surface
of the water.

pokemon.name: Seadra
pokemon.blurb:
Capable of swimÂ­
ming backwards by
rapidly flapping its wing-like
pectoral fins and
stout tail.

pokemon.name: Goldeen
pokemon.blurb:
Its tail fin
billows like an
elegant ballroom dress, giving it
the nickname of
the Water Queen.

pokemon.name: Seaking
pokemon.blurb:
In the autumn
spawning season,
they can be seen swimming powerÂ­
fully up rivers
and creeks.

pokemon.name: Staryu
pokemon.blurb:
An enigmatic
POKÃ©MON that can
effortlessly regenerate any
appendage it
loses in battle.

pokemon.name: Starmie
pokemon.blurb:
Its central core
glows with the
seven colors of the rainbow. Some
people value the
core as a gem.

pokemon.name: Mr-mime
pokemon.blurb:
If interrupted
while it is
miming, it will slap around the
offender with its
broad hands.

pokemon.name: Scyther
pokemon.blurb:
With ninja-like
agility and speed,
it can create the illusion that
there is more
than one.

pokemon.name: Jynx
pokemon.blurb:
It seductively
wiggles its hips
as it walks. It can cause people
to dance in
unison with it.

pokemon.name: Electabuzz
pokemon.blurb:
Normally found
near power plants,
they can wander away and cause
major blackouts
in cities.

pokemon.name: Magmar
pokemon.blurb:
Its body always
burns with an
orange glow that enables it to
hide perfectly
among flames.

pokemon.name: Pinsir
pokemon.blurb:
If it fails to
crush the victim
in its pincers, it will swing it
around and toss
it hard.

pokemon.name: Tauros
pokemon.blurb:
When it targets
an enemy, it
charges furiously while whipping its
body with its
long tails.

pokemon.name: Magikarp
pokemon.blurb:
In the distant
past, it was
somewhat stronger than the horribly
weak descendants
that exist today.

pokemon.name: Gyarados
pokemon.blurb:
Rarely seen in
the wild. Huge
and vicious, it is capable of
destroying entire
cities in a rage.

pokemon.name: Lapras
pokemon.blurb:
A POKÃ©MON that
has been overÂ­
hunted almost to extinction. It
can ferry people
across the water.

pokemon.name: Ditto
pokemon.blurb:
Capable of copying
an enemy's genetic
code to instantly transform itself
into a duplicate
of the enemy.

pokemon.name: Eevee
pokemon.blurb:
Its genetic code
is irregular.
It may mutate if it is exposed to
radiation from
element STONEs.

pokemon.name: Vaporeon
pokemon.blurb:
Lives close to
water. Its long
tail is ridged with a fin which
is often mistaken
for a mermaid's.

pokemon.name: Jolteon
pokemon.blurb:
It accumulates
negative ions in
the atmosphere to blast out 10000-
volt lightning
bolts.

pokemon.name: Flareon
pokemon.blurb:
When storing
thermal energy in
its body, its temperature could
soar to over 1600
degrees.

pokemon.name: Porygon
pokemon.blurb:
A POKÃ©MON that
consists entirely
of programming code. Capable of
moving freely in
cyberspace.

pokemon.name: Omanyte
pokemon.blurb:
Although long
extinct, in rare
cases, it can be genetically
resurrected from
fossils.

pokemon.name: Omastar
pokemon.blurb:
A prehistoric
POKÃ©MON that died
out when its heavy shell made
it impossible to
catch prey.

pokemon.name: Kabuto
pokemon.blurb:
A POKÃ©MON that
was resurrected
from a fossil found in what was
once the ocean
floor eons ago.

pokemon.name: Kabutops
pokemon.blurb:
Its sleek shape is
perfect for swimÂ­
ming. It slashes prey with its
claws and drains
the body fluids.

pokemon.name: Aerodactyl
pokemon.blurb:
A ferocious, preÂ­
historic POKÃ©MON
that goes for the enemy's throat
with its serrated
saw-like fangs.

pokemon.name: Snorlax
pokemon.blurb:
Very lazy. Just
eats and sleeps.
As its rotund bulk builds, it
becomes steadily
more slothful.

pokemon.name: Articuno
pokemon.blurb:
A legendary bird
POKÃ©MON that is
said to appear to doomed people who
are lost in icy
mountains.

pokemon.name: Zapdos
pokemon.blurb:
A legendary bird
POKÃ©MON that is
said to appear from clouds while
dropping enormous
lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: Moltres
pokemon.blurb:
Legendary bird
POKÃ©MON. It is
said to migrate from the south
along with the
spring.

pokemon.name: Dratini
pokemon.blurb:
Long considered a
mythical POKÃ©MON
until recently when a small
colony was found
living underwater.

pokemon.name: Dragonair
pokemon.blurb:
A mystical POKÃ©MON
that exudes a
gentle aura. Has the ability
to change climate
conditions.

pokemon.name: Dragonite
pokemon.blurb:
An extremely
rarely seen
marine POKÃ©MON. Its intelligence
is said to match
that of humans.

pokemon.name: Mewtwo
pokemon.blurb:
It was created by
a scientist after
years of horrific gene splicing and
DNA engineering
experiments.

pokemon.name: Mew
pokemon.blurb:
So rare that it
is still said to
be a mirage by many experts. Only
a few people have
seen it worldwide.

pokemon.name: Chikorita
pokemon.blurb:
A sweet aroma
gently wafts from
the leaf on its head. It is docile
and loves to soak
up the sun's rays.

pokemon.name: Bayleef
pokemon.blurb:
The buds that ring its neck give
off a spicy aroma that perks
people up.

pokemon.name: Meganium
pokemon.blurb:
Its breath has the fantastic
ability to revive dead plants and
flowers.

pokemon.name: Cyndaquil
pokemon.blurb:
It is timid, and
always curls itÂ­
self up in a ball. If attacked, it
flares up its back
for protection.

pokemon.name: Quilava
pokemon.blurb:
Be careful if it
turns its back
during battle. It means that it will
attack with the
fire on its back.

pokemon.name: Typhlosion
pokemon.blurb:
If its rage peaks,
it becomes so hot
that anything that touches it will
instantly go
up in flames.

pokemon.name: Totodile
pokemon.blurb:
Its well-developed
jaws are powerful
and capable of crushing anything.
Even its trainer
must be careful.

pokemon.name: Croconaw
pokemon.blurb:
If it loses a
fang, a new one
grows back in its place. There are
always 48 fangs
lining its mouth.

pokemon.name: Feraligatr
pokemon.blurb:
When it bites with
its massive and
powerful jaws, it shakes its head
and savagely tears
its victim up.

pokemon.name: Sentret
pokemon.blurb:
It has a very nervous nature.
It stands up high on its tail so it
can scan wide areas.

pokemon.name: Furret
pokemon.blurb:
It makes a nest to
suit its long and
skinny body. The nest is impossible
for other POKÃ©MON
to enter.

pokemon.name: Hoothoot
pokemon.blurb:
It always stands
on one foot. It
changes feet so fast, the movement

seen.

pokemon.name: Noctowl
pokemon.blurb:
Its eyes are
specially adapted.
They concentrate even faint light
and enable it to
see in the dark.

pokemon.name: Ledyba
pokemon.blurb:
It is very timid.
It will be afraid
to move if it is alone. But it will
be active if it is
in a group.

pokemon.name: Ledian
pokemon.blurb:
When the stars
flicker in the
night sky, it flutters about,
scattering a
glowing powder.

pokemon.name: Spinarak
pokemon.blurb:
It lies still in
the same pose for

unsuspecting prey
to wander close.

pokemon.name: Crobat

lently through the

pokemon.name: Chinchou

tricity between the tips of its

Lanturnâs light can shine up from

pokemon.name: Cleffa
pokemon.blurb:
Because of its
unusual, star-like

a meteor.

pokemon.name: Igglybuff

It has a very soft

to stop.

pokemon.name: Togepi
pokemon.blurb:
The shell seems to
be filled with
joy. It is said that it will share

treated kindly.

pokemon.name: Togetic

hearted people.

pokemon.name: Natu

Because its wings

grown, it has to hop to get around.

ing at something.

pokemon.name: Xatu

They say that it

quiet because it is seeing both the
past and future at
the same time.

pokemon.name: Mareep

If static elecÂ­
tricity builds in
its body, its fleece doubles in
volume. Touching

pokemon.name: Flaaffy

As a result of
storing too much
electricity, it developed patches
where even downy
wool won't grow.

pokemon.name: Ampharos
pokemon.blurb:
The tail's tip
shines brightly
and can be seen from far away. It

for lost people.

pokemon.name: Bellossom
pokemon.blurb:
BELLOSSOM gather
at times and
appear to dance. They say that the
dance is a ritual
to summon the sun.

pokemon.name: Marill
pokemon.blurb:
The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can
stay dry, even when it plays in the water.

pokemon.name: Azumarill

By keeping still
and listening inÂ­
tently, it can tell what is in
even wild, fast-

pokemon.name: Sudowoodo

Although it always
pretends to be a

pokemon.name: Politoed

If POLIWAG and
POLIWHIRL hear its

ing from far and
wide.

pokemon.name: Hoppip

To keep from being
blown away by the
wind, they gather in clusters. They

breezes, though.

pokemon.name: Skiploom
pokemon.blurb:
The bloom on top
of its head opens
and closes as the temperature flucÂ­
tuates up and
down.

pokemon.name: Jumpluff
pokemon.blurb:
Blown by seasonal winds, it
circles the globe, scattering
cotton spores as it goes.

pokemon.name: Aipom
pokemon.blurb:
Its tail is so
powerful that it
can use it to grab a tree branch and
hold itself up in
the air.

pokemon.name: Sunkern
pokemon.blurb:
It may drop out of
the sky suddenly.
If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will
violently shake
its leaves.

pokemon.name: Sunflora
pokemon.blurb:
It converts sunÂ­
light into energy.
In the darkness after sunset, it
closes its petals
and becomes still.

pokemon.name: Yanma
pokemon.blurb:
If it flaps its
wings really fast,

dows in the area.

pokemon.name: Wooper
pokemon.blurb:
When it walks aÂ­
round on the

film.

pokemon.name: Quagsire
pokemon.blurb:
This carefree
POKÃ©MON has an
easy-going nature. While swimming, it

pokemon.name: Espeon
pokemon.blurb:
It uses the fine
hair that covers
its body to sense air currents and

my's actions.

pokemon.name: Umbreon
pokemon.blurb:
When agitated,
this POKÃ©MON proÂ­

sweat from its

pokemon.name: Murkrow
pokemon.blurb:
Feared and loathed
by many, it is
believed to bring misfortune to all
those who see it
at night.

pokemon.name: Slowking
pokemon.blurb:
It has incredible
intellect and inÂ­
tuition. Whatever the situation, it
remains calm and
collected.

pokemon.name: Misdreavus
pokemon.blurb:
It likes playing
mischievous tricks
such as screaming and wailing to
startle people at
night.

pokemon.name: Unown
pokemon.blurb:
Their shapes look
like hieroglyphs
on ancient tabÂ­ lets. It is said
that the two are
somehow related.

pokemon.name: Wobbuffet

It hates light and

ed, it inflates its body to pump

strike.

pokemon.name: Girafarig

Its tail has a

pokemon.name: Pineco
pokemon.blurb:
It likes to make
its shell thicker

additional weight

pokemon.name: Forretress
pokemon.blurb:
Its entire body is
shielded by a
steel-hard shell. What lurks inside

total mystery.

pokemon.name: Dunsparce

When spotted, this

at its target's

tled victim to
inject poison.

pokemon.name: Steelix
pokemon.blurb:
The iron it ingested with the soil it
swallowed transformed its body and
made it harder than diamonds.

pokemon.name: Snubbull
pokemon.blurb:
Although it looks
frightening, it is
actually kind and affectionate. It
is very popular
among women.

pokemon.name: Granbull
pokemon.blurb:
It is actually
timid and easily
spooked. If atÂ­ tacked, it flails
about to fend off
its attacker.

pokemon.name: Qwilfish
pokemon.blurb:
To fire its poison
spikes, it must
inflate its body by drinking over
2.6 gallons of
water all at once.

pokemon.name: Scizor
pokemon.blurb:
It swings its eye-
patterned pincers
up to scare its foes. This makes
it look like it
has three heads.

pokemon.name: Shuckle
pokemon.blurb:
The BERRIES it
stores in its
vase-like shell decompose and
become a gooey
liquid.

pokemon.name: Heracross
pokemon.blurb:
This powerful
POKÃ©MON thrusts
its prized horn under its enemiesâ

and throws them.

pokemon.name: Sneasel

Its paws conceal
sharp claws. If
attacked, it sudÂ­ denly extends the
claws and startles
its enemy.

pokemon.name: Teddiursa
pokemon.blurb:
If it finds honey,
its crescent mark
glows. It always licks its paws
because they are
soaked with honey.

pokemon.name: Ursaring
pokemon.blurb:
Although it is a
good climber, it
prefers to snap trees with its
forelegs and eat
fallen BERRIES.

pokemon.name: Slugma
pokemon.blurb:
It never sleeps.
It has to keep
moving because if it stopped, its
magma body would
cool and harden.

pokemon.name: Magcargo
pokemon.blurb:
The shell on its
back is just skin
that has cooled and hardened. It
breaks easily with
a slight touch.

pokemon.name: Swinub
pokemon.blurb:
It rubs its snout
on the ground to
find and dig up food. It sometimes
discovers hot
springs.

pokemon.name: Piloswine
pokemon.blurb:
Because the long
hair all over its
body obscures its sight, it just
keeps charging
repeatedly.

pokemon.name: Corsola
pokemon.blurb:
They prefer unpolluted southern seas.
Their coral branches lose their color
and deteriorate in dirty water.

pokemon.name: Remoraid
pokemon.blurb:
It has superb acÂ­
curacy. The water
it shoots out can strike even moving
prey from more
than 300 feet.

pokemon.name: Octillery
pokemon.blurb:
It traps enemies
with its suction-
cupped tentacles then smashes them
with its rock-hard
head.

pokemon.name: Delibird
pokemon.blurb:
It carries food
all day long.
There are tales about lost people
who were saved by
the food it had.

pokemon.name: Mantine
pokemon.blurb:
As it majestically
swims, it doesn't
care if REMORAID attach to it for
scavenging its
leftovers.

pokemon.name: Skarmory
pokemon.blurb:
Its sturdy wings
look heavy, but
they are actually hollow and light,
allowing it to fly
freely in the sky.

pokemon.name: Houndour
pokemon.blurb:
It uses different
kinds of cries for
communicating with others of its kind
and for pursuing
its prey.

pokemon.name: Houndoom
pokemon.blurb:
If you are burned
by the flames it
shoots from its mouth, the pain
will never go
away.

pokemon.name: Kingdra
pokemon.blurb:
It is said that it usually hides in
underwater caves. It can create
whirlpools by yawning.

pokemon.name: Phanpy
pokemon.blurb:
It swings its long
snout around playÂ­
fully, but because it is so strong,
that can be danÂ­
gerous.

pokemon.name: Donphan
pokemon.blurb:
It has sharp, hard
tusks and a rugged
hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough
to knock down a
house.

pokemon.name: Porygon2
pokemon.blurb:
This upgraded
version of PORYGON
is designed for space exploration.
It can't fly,
though.

pokemon.name: Stantler
pokemon.blurb:
The curved antlers
subtly change the
flow of air to create a strange
space where realÂ­
ity is distorted.

pokemon.name: Smeargle
pokemon.blurb:
A special fluid
oozes from the tip
of its tail. It paints the fluid
everywhere to mark
its territory.

pokemon.name: Tyrogue
pokemon.blurb:
It is always
bursting with enÂ­
ergy. To make itÂ­ self stronger, it
keeps on fighting
even if it loses.

pokemon.name: Hitmontop
pokemon.blurb:
If you become
enchanted by its
smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks,
you may get
drilled hard.

pokemon.name: Smoochum
pokemon.blurb:
Its lips are the
most sensitive
parts on its body. It always uses its
lips first to
examine things.

pokemon.name: Elekid
pokemon.blurb:
It rotates its
arms to generate
electricity, but it tires easily,
so it charges up
only a little bit.

pokemon.name: Magby
pokemon.blurb:
Each and every
time it inhales
and exhales, hot embers dribble out
of its mouth and
nostrils.

pokemon.name: Miltank
pokemon.blurb:
Its milk is packed
with nutrition,
making it the ultimate beverage
for the sick or
weary.

pokemon.name: Blissey
pokemon.blurb:
Anyone who takes
even one bite of
BLISSEY's egg beÂ­ comes unfailingly
caring and pleasÂ­
ant to everyone.

pokemon.name: Raikou
pokemon.blurb:
The rain clouds it
carries let it
fire thunderbolts at will. They say
that it descended
with lightning.

pokemon.name: Entei
pokemon.blurb:
Volcanoes erupt
when it barks. UnÂ­
able to restrain its extreme power,
it races headlong
around the land.

pokemon.name: Suicune
pokemon.blurb:
Said to be the
reincarnation of
north winds, it can instantly
purify filthy,
murky water.

pokemon.name: Larvitar
pokemon.blurb:
It feeds on soil.
After it has eaten
a large mountain, it will fall
asleep so it can
grow.

pokemon.name: Pupitar
pokemon.blurb:
Its shell is as
hard as sheet
rock, and it is also very strong.
Its THRASHING can
topple a mountain.

pokemon.name: Tyranitar
pokemon.blurb:
Its body can't be
harmed by any sort
of attack, so it is very eager to
make challenges
against enemies.

pokemon.name: Lugia
pokemon.blurb:
It is said that it
quietly spends its
time deep at the bottom of the sea
because its powers
are too strong.

pokemon.name: Ho-oh
pokemon.blurb:
Legends claim this
POKÃ©MON flies the
world's skies conÂ­ tinuously on its
magnificent seven-
colored wings.

pokemon.name: Celebi

This POKÃ©MON wanÂ­
ders across time.
Grass and trees flourish in the
forests in which
it has appeared.

pokemon.name: Treecko

TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom
of its feet that enable it to scale
vertical walls. This POKÃ©MON attacks by slamming foes
with its thick tail.

pokemon.name: Grovyle

The leaves growing out of GROVYLEâs

it from enemies in the forest. This POKÃ©MON is a master at climbing
trees in jungles.

pokemon.name: Sceptile

The leaves growing on SCEPTILEâs body
are very sharp edged. This POKÃ©MON is
very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe
from above or behind.

pokemon.name: Torchic

TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER,
following behind with unsteady
steps. This POKÃ©MON breathes fire of over
1,800 degrees F, including fireballs
that leave the foe scorched black.

pokemon.name: Combusken

COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and
thighs by running through fields and
mountains. This POKÃ©MONâs legs possess both speed
and power, enabling it to dole out ten
kicks in one second.

pokemon.name: Blaziken

In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense
flames from its wrists and attacks foes
courageously. The stronger the foe, the more
intensely this POKÃ©MONâs wrists burn.

pokemon.name: Mudkip

The fin on MUDKIPâs head acts as highly
sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense
movements of water and air, this POKÃ©MON can determine what is taking

pokemon.name: Marshtomp

The surface of MARSHTOMPâs body is
enveloped by a thin, sticky film that
enables it to live on land. This POKÃ©MON plays in mud on beaches
when the ocean tide is low.

pokemon.name: Swampert

SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough
power to easily drag a boulder weighing
more than a ton. This POKÃ©MON also has powerful vision
that lets it see even in murky water.

pokemon.name: Poochyena
pokemon.blurb:
At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite
at anything that moves.
This POKÃ©MON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted.
However, it may turn tail if the prey
strikes back.

pokemon.name: Mightyena
pokemon.blurb:
MIGHTYENA gives obvious signals when
it is preparing to attack. It starts to
growl deeply and then flattens its body. This POKÃ©MON will bite savagely with its
sharply pointed fangs.

pokemon.name: Zigzagoon
pokemon.blurb:
ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders
everywhere at all times. This POKÃ©MON
does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything
that it happens to see.

pokemon.name: Linoone

LINOONE always runs full speed and only
in straight lines. If facing an obstacle,
it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKÃ©MON is very challenged by
gently curving roads.

pokemon.name: Wurmple

Using the spikes on its rear end,  
WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and
feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKÃ©MONâs feet are tipped with
suction pads that allow it to cling to

pokemon.name: Silcoon

SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch

this POKÃ©MON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution.
It peers out of the silk cocoon through
a small hole.

pokemon.name: Beautifly

BEAUTIFLYâs favorite food is the sweet
pollen of flowers. If you want to see

pokemon.name: Cascoon

CASCOON makes its protective cocoon
by wrapping its body entirely with a
fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens.
This POKÃ©MON prepares for its evolution
inside the cocoon.

pokemon.name: Dustox
pokemon.blurb:
DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light.
Swarms of this POKÃ©MON are attracted
by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the
leaves off roadside trees for food.

pokemon.name: Lotad
pokemon.blurb:
It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry
to PokÃ©mon that canât swim.

pokemon.name: Lombre

LOMBRE is nocturnal - it will get active
after dusk. It is also a mischief-maker.
When this POKÃ©MON spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from
beneath the surface and enjoys their
consternation.

pokemon.name: Ludicolo
pokemon.blurb:
LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as
it hears cheerful, festive music.
This POKÃ©MON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking
outings.

pokemon.name: Seedot
pokemon.blurb:
SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree
branch using the top of its head.
It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch.
The more water it drinks, the glossier
this POKÃ©MONâs body becomes.

pokemon.name: Nuzleaf
pokemon.blurb:
NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown
forests. They occasionally venture out
of the forest to startle people. This POKÃ©MON dislikes having its long
nose pinched.

pokemon.name: Shiftry
pokemon.blurb:
SHIFTRY is a mysterious POKÃ©MON that
is said to live atop towering trees 
dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with
the fans it holds.

pokemon.name: Taillow
pokemon.blurb:
It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on
tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

pokemon.name: Swellow
pokemon.blurb:
SWELLOW flies high above our heads,
making graceful arcs in the sky.
This POKÃ©MON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless
prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOWâs

pokemon.name: Wingull
pokemon.blurb:
WINGULL has the habit of carrying prey
and valuables in its beak and hiding
them in all sorts of locations. This POKÃ©MON rides the winds and flies
as if it were skating across the sky.

pokemon.name: Pelipper
pokemon.blurb:
It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small
PokÃ©mon and eggs to safety in its bill.

pokemon.name: Ralts
pokemon.blurb:
RALTS senses the emotions of
people using the horns on its head.
This POKÃ©MON rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws
closer if it senses that the person has
a positive disposition.

pokemon.name: Kirlia
pokemon.blurb:
If its Trainer becomes happy, it
overflows with energy, dancing
joyously while spinning about.

pokemon.name: Gardevoir
pokemon.blurb:
GARDEVOIR has the ability to read the
future. If it senses impending danger
to its TRAINER, this POKÃ©MON is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at
full power.

pokemon.name: Surskit
pokemon.blurb:
From the tips of its feet, SURSKIT
secretes an oil that enables it to walk
on water as if it were skating. This POKÃ©MON feeds on microscopic
organisms in ponds and lakes.

pokemon.name: Masquerain
pokemon.blurb:
MASQUERAIN intimidates enemies with
the eyelike patterns on its antennas.
This POKÃ©MON flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction - even
sideways and backwards - as if it were
a helicopter.

pokemon.name: Shroomish
pokemon.blurb:
SHROOMISH live in damp soil in the dark
depths of forests. They are often
found keeping still under fallen leaves. This POKÃ©MON feeds on compost that
is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

pokemon.name: Breloom
pokemon.blurb:
BRELOOM closes in on its foe with light
and sprightly footwork, then throws
punches with its stretchy arms. This POKÃ©MONâs fighting technique puts
boxers to shame.

pokemon.name: Slakoth
pokemon.blurb:
SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty
hours every day. Because it moves so
little, it does not need much food. This POKÃ©MONâs sole daily meal consists
of just three leaves.

pokemon.name: Vigoroth
pokemon.blurb:
Its heart beats at a tenfold
tempo, so it cannot sit still for
even a moment.

pokemon.name: Slaking
pokemon.blurb:
SLAKING spends all day lying down and
lolling about.
It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach,
this POKÃ©MON reluctantly moves to
another spot.

pokemon.name: Nincada
pokemon.blurb:
NINCADA lives underground for many
years in complete darkness.
This POKÃ©MON absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless
as it waits for evolution.

pokemon.name: Ninjask
pokemon.blurb:
NINJASK moves around at such a high
speed that it cannot be seen, even
while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this POKÃ©MON was long
believed to be invisible.

pokemon.name: Shedinja
pokemon.blurb:
SHEDINJAâs hard body doesnât move -
not even a twitch. In fact, its body
appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this POKÃ©MON will
steal the spirit of anyone peering into
its hollow body from its back.

pokemon.name: Whismur
pokemon.blurb:
Normally, WHISMURâs voice is very quiet -
it is barely audible even if one is
paying close attention. However, if this POKÃ©MON senses danger,
it starts crying at an earsplitting
volume.

pokemon.name: Loudred
pokemon.blurb:
LOUDREDâs bellowing can completely
decimate a wood-frame house. It uses
its voice to punish its foes. This POKÃ©MONâs round ears serve as
loudspeakers.

pokemon.name: Exploud
pokemon.blurb:
EXPLOUD triggers earthquakes with the
tremors it creates by bellowing. If this
POKÃ©MON violently inhales from the ports on its body, itâs a sign that it is
preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

pokemon.name: Makuhita
pokemon.blurb:
MAKUHITA is tenacious - it will keep
getting up and attacking its foe
however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this
POKÃ©MON stores more energy in its body
for evolving.

pokemon.name: Hariyama
pokemon.blurb:
HARIYAMA practices its straight-arm
slaps in any number of locations.
One hit of this POKÃ©MONâs powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches
could snap a telephone pole in two.

pokemon.name: Azurill
pokemon.blurb:
AZURILL spins its tail as if it were a
lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum
of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these
POKÃ©MON managed to hurl itself a record
33 feet.

pokemon.name: Nosepass
pokemon.blurb:
NOSEPASSâs magnetic nose is always
pointed to the north. If two of these
POKÃ©MON meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they
are close because their magnetic noses
repel one another.

pokemon.name: Skitty
pokemon.blurb:
SKITTY has the habit of becoming
fascinated by moving objects and
chasing them around. This POKÃ©MON is known to chase after
its own tail and become dizzy.

pokemon.name: Delcatty
pokemon.blurb:
DELCATTY prefers to live an unfettered
existence in which it can do as it
pleases at its own pace. Because this POKÃ©MON eats and sleeps
whenever it decides, its daily routines
are completely random.

pokemon.name: Sableye
pokemon.blurb:
SABLEYE lead quiet lives deep inside
caverns. They are feared, however,
because these POKÃ©MON are thought to steal the spirits of people when their
eyes burn with a sinister glow in the
darkness.

pokemon.name: Mawile
pokemon.blurb:
MAWHILEâs huge jaws are actually steel
horns that have been transformed.
Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard.
When the foe least expects it, MAWHILE
chomps it with its gaping jaws.

pokemon.name: Aron
pokemon.blurb:
This POKÃ©MON has a body of steel.
To make its body, ARON feeds on
iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by
eating bridges and rails.

pokemon.name: Lairon
pokemon.blurb:
LAIRON tempers its steel body by
drinking highly nutritious mineral
springwater until it is bloated. This POKÃ©MON makes its nest close to
springs of delicious water.

pokemon.name: Aggron
pokemon.blurb:
AGGRON claims an entire mountain as its
own territory. It mercilessly beats up
anything that violates its environment. This POKÃ©MON vigilantly patrols its
territory at all times.

pokemon.name: Meditite
pokemon.blurb:
MEDITITE undertakes rigorous mental
training deep in the mountains.
However, whenever it meditates, this POKÃ©MON always loses its concentration
and focus. As a result, its training
never ends.

pokemon.name: Medicham
pokemon.blurb:
It gains the ability to see the aura
of its opponents by honing its mind
through starvation.

pokemon.name: Electrike
pokemon.blurb:
ELECTRIKE stores electricity in its
long body hair. This POKÃ©MON stimulates
its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs
explosive acceleration performance.

pokemon.name: Manectric
pokemon.blurb:
MANECTRIC is constantly discharging
electricity from its mane. The sparks
sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this POKÃ©MON
creates thunderclouds.

pokemon.name: Plusle
pokemon.blurb:
PLUSLE always acts as a cheerleader
for its partners. Whenever a teammate
puts out a good effort in battle, this POKÃ©MON shorts out its body to create
the crackling noises of sparks to show
its joy.

pokemon.name: Minun
pokemon.blurb:
MINUN is more concerned about cheering
on its partners than its own safety.
It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of
sparks to cheer on its teammates.

pokemon.name: Volbeat
pokemon.blurb:
With the arrival of night, VOLBEAT emits
light from its tail. It communicates with
others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light.
This POKÃ©MON is attracted by the sweet
aroma of ILLUMISE.

pokemon.name: Illumise
pokemon.blurb:
ILLUMISE attracts a swarm of VOLBEAT
using a sweet fragrance. Once the
VOLBEAT have gathered, this POKÃ©MON leads the lit-up swarm in drawing
geometric designs on the canvas of
the night sky.

pokemon.name: Roselia
pokemon.blurb:
ROSELIA shoots sharp thorns as
projectiles at any opponent that tries
to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this POKÃ©MON brings
serenity to living things.

pokemon.name: Gulpin
pokemon.blurb:
Virtually all of GULPINâs body is its
stomach. As a result, it can swallow
something its own size. This POKÃ©MONâs stomach contains a
special fluid that digests anything.

pokemon.name: Swalot
pokemon.blurb:
It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids
from its follicles to douse foes.

pokemon.name: Carvanha
pokemon.blurb:
CARVANHAâs strongly developed jaws
and its sharply pointed fangs pack the
destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and
sunk by this POKÃ©MON.

pokemon.name: Sharpedo
pokemon.blurb:
Nicknamed âthe bully of the sea,â
SHARPEDO is widely feared.
Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off.
Just one of these POKÃ©MON can
thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

pokemon.name: Wailmer
pokemon.blurb:
WAILMERâs nostrils are located above
its eyes. This playful POKÃ©MON loves
to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body
out of its nostrils.

pokemon.name: Wailord
pokemon.blurb:
WAILORD is the largest of all identified
POKÃ©MON up to now.
This giant POKÃ©MON swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive
amounts of food at once with its
enormous mouth.

pokemon.name: Numel
pokemon.blurb:
NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it
doesnât notice being hit. However, it
canât stand hunger for even a second. This POKÃ©MONâs body is a seething
cauldron of boiling magma.

pokemon.name: Camerupt
pokemon.blurb:
CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body.
Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses
through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this
POKÃ©MONâs back erupt, spewing the
superheated magma.

pokemon.name: Torkoal
pokemon.blurb:
TORKOAL digs through mountains in
search of coal. If it finds some, it fills
hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it.
If it is attacked, this POKÃ©MON spouts
thick black smoke to beat a retreat.

pokemon.name: Spoink
pokemon.blurb:
SPOINK bounces around on its tail.
The shock of its bouncing makes its
heart pump. As a result, this POKÃ©MON cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it
stops, its heart will stop.

pokemon.name: Grumpig
pokemon.blurb:
GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its
body to amplify its psychic power waves
for gaining total control over its foe. When this POKÃ©MON uses its special
power, its snorting breath grows
labored.

pokemon.name: Spinda
pokemon.blurb:
No two SPINDA have the same
pattern of spots. Its tottering
step fouls the aim of foes.

pokemon.name: Trapinch
pokemon.blurb:
TRAPINCHâs nest is a sloped, bowl-like
pit dug in sand. This POKÃ©MON patiently
waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength
to crush even boulders.

pokemon.name: Vibrava
pokemon.blurb:
To make prey faint, VIBRAVA generates
ultrasonic waves by vigorously making
its two wings vibrate. This POKÃ©MONâs ultrasonic waves are so
powerful, they can bring on headaches
in people.

pokemon.name: Flygon
pokemon.blurb:
FLYGON is nicknamed âthe elemental 
spirit of the desert.â Because its
flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this POKÃ©MON is always enveloped in a
sandstorm while flying.

pokemon.name: Cacnea
pokemon.blurb:
CACNEA lives in arid locations such
as deserts. It releases a strong aroma
from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this POKÃ©MON
shoots sharp thorns from its body to
bring the victim down.

pokemon.name: Cacturne
pokemon.blurb:
During the daytime, CACTURNE remains
unmoving so that it does not lose any
moisture to the harsh desert sun. This POKÃ©MON becomes active at night
when the temperature drops.

pokemon.name: Swablu
pokemon.blurb:
SWABLU has light and fluffy wings that
are like cottony clouds. This POKÃ©MON
is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and
sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

pokemon.name: Altaria
pokemon.blurb:
It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic
humming makes you feel like youâre in a dream.

pokemon.name: Zangoose
pokemon.blurb:
Memories of battling its arch-rival
SEVIPER are etched into every cell of
ZANGOOSEâs body. This POKÃ©MON adroitly dodges attacks
with incredible agility.

pokemon.name: Seviper
pokemon.blurb:
SEVIPER shares a generations-long
feud with ZANGOOSE. The scars on its
body are evidence of vicious battles. This POKÃ©MON attacks using its sword-
edged tail.

pokemon.name: Lunatone
pokemon.blurb:
LUNATONE was discovered at a location
where a meteorite fell. As a result, some
people theorize that this POKÃ©MON came from space. However, no one has
been able to prove this theory so far.

pokemon.name: Solrock
pokemon.blurb:
A new PokÃ©mon species, rumored
to be from the sun. It gives off
light while spinning.

pokemon.name: Barboach
pokemon.blurb:
BARBOACHâs sensitive whiskers serve
as a superb radar system.
This POKÃ©MON hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits
for prey to come along.

pokemon.name: Whiscash
pokemon.blurb:
WHISCASH is extremely territorial.
Just one of these POKÃ©MON will claim a
large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes
about and triggers a massive
earthquake.

pokemon.name: Corphish
pokemon.blurb:
CORPHISH were originally foreign
POKÃ©MON that were imported as pets.
They eventually turned up in the wild. This POKÃ©MON is very hardy and has
greatly increased its population.

pokemon.name: Crawdaunt
pokemon.blurb:
CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent
nature that compels it to challenge
other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in
ponds inhabited by this POKÃ©MON,
making them desolate places.

pokemon.name: Baltoy
pokemon.blurb:
BALTOY moves while spinning around on
its one foot. Primitive wall paintings
depicting this POKÃ©MON living among people were discovered in some ancient
ruins.

pokemon.name: Claydol
pokemon.blurb:
CLAYDOL are said to be dolls of mud made
by primitive humans and brought to life
by exposure to a mysterious ray. This POKÃ©MON moves about while
levitating.

pokemon.name: Lileep
pokemon.blurb:
LILEEP became extinct approximately
a hundred million years ago.
This ancient POKÃ©MON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches
approaching prey using tentacles 
shaped like flower petals.

pokemon.name: Cradily
pokemon.blurb:
CRADILY roams around the ocean floor
in search of food. This POKÃ©MON freely
extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight
tentacles.

pokemon.name: Anorith
pokemon.blurb:
ANORITH was regenerated from a
prehistoric fossil. This primitive
POKÃ©MON once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its
two large claws.

pokemon.name: Armaldo
pokemon.blurb:
ARMALDOâs tough armor makes all attacks
bounce off. This POKÃ©MONâs two
enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to
punch right through a steel slab.

pokemon.name: Feebas
pokemon.blurb:
FEEBASâs fins are ragged and
tattered from the start of its life.
Because of its shoddy appearance, this POKÃ©MON is largely ignored.
It is capable of living in both the sea
and in rivers.

pokemon.name: Milotic
pokemon.blurb:
MILOTIC is said to be the most
beautiful of all the POKÃ©MON.
It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell
bitter feuding.

pokemon.name: Castform
pokemon.blurb:
CASTFORMâs appearance changes with
the weather.
This POKÃ©MON gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect
its tiny body.

pokemon.name: Kecleon
pokemon.blurb:
KECLEON is capable of changing its body
colors at will to blend in with its
surroundings. There is one exception - this POKÃ©MON
canât change the zigzag pattern on its
belly.

pokemon.name: Shuppet
pokemon.blurb:
Thereâs a proverb that says, âShun the house
where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk.â

pokemon.name: Banette
pokemon.blurb:
BANETTE generates energy for laying
strong curses by sticking pins into its
own body. This POKÃ©MON was originally a pitiful
plush doll that was thrown away.

pokemon.name: Duskull
pokemon.blurb:
DUSKULL can pass through any wall no
matter how thick it may be.
Once this POKÃ©MON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended
victim until the break of dawn.

pokemon.name: Dusclops
pokemon.blurb:
DUSCLOPSâs body is completely hollow -
there is nothing at all inside.
It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKÃ©MON will absorb anything
into its body, but nothing will ever come
back out.

pokemon.name: Tropius
pokemon.blurb:
The bunches of fruit around TROPIUSâs
neck are very popular with children.
This POKÃ©MON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for
fruit resulted in its own outgrowth
of fruit.

pokemon.name: Chimecho
pokemon.blurb:
CHIMECHO makes its cries echo
inside its hollow body. When this
POKÃ©MON becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have
the power to knock foes flying.

pokemon.name: Absol
pokemon.blurb:
Every time ABSOL appears before people,
it is followed by a disaster such as an
earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the
disaster POKÃ©MON.

pokemon.name: Wynaut
pokemon.blurb:
WYNAUT can always be seen with a big,
happy smile on its face. Look at its tail
to determine if it is angry. When angered, this POKÃ©MON will be
slapping the ground with its tail.

pokemon.name: Snorunt
pokemon.blurb:
SNORUNT live in regions with heavy
snowfall. In seasons without snow, such
as spring and summer, this POKÃ©MON steals away to live quietly among
stalactites and stalagmites deep in
caverns.

pokemon.name: Glalie
pokemon.blurb:
GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it
hardens with an armor of ice.
This POKÃ©MON has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any
shape it desires.

pokemon.name: Spheal
pokemon.blurb:
SPHEAL is much faster rolling than 
walking to get around. When groups of
this POKÃ©MON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this,
their mealtimes are noisy.

pokemon.name: Sealeo
pokemon.blurb:
SEALEO has the habit of always juggling
on the tip of its nose anything it sees
for the first time. This POKÃ©MON occasionally entertains
itself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL
on its nose.

pokemon.name: Walrein
pokemon.blurb:
WALREINâs two massively developed
tusks can totally shatter blocks of
ice weighing ten tons with one blow. This POKÃ©MONâs thick coat of blubber
insulates it from subzero temperatures.

pokemon.name: Clamperl
pokemon.blurb:
CLAMPERLâs sturdy shell is not only good
for protection - it is also used for
clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERLâs shell will be
scored with nicks and scratches all
over.

pokemon.name: Huntail
pokemon.blurb:
HUNTAILâs presence went unnoticed by
people for a long time because it lives
at extreme depths in the sea. This POKÃ©MONâs eyes can see clearly
even in the murky dark depths of the
ocean.

pokemon.name: Gorebyss
pokemon.blurb:
GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas
at extreme depths. Its body is built to
withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of
this, this POKÃ©MONâs body is unharmed
by ordinary attacks.

pokemon.name: Relicanth
pokemon.blurb:
RELICANTH is a POKÃ©MON species that
existed for a hundred million years
without ever changing its form. This ancient POKÃ©MON feeds on
microscopic organisms with its
toothless mouth.

pokemon.name: Luvdisc
pokemon.blurb:
LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the
tropics. This heart-shaped POKÃ©MON
earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the
oceanâs waves.

pokemon.name: Bagon
pokemon.blurb:
BAGON has a dream of one day soaring
in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly,
this POKÃ©MON hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has 
grown tough and as hard as tempered
steel.

pokemon.name: Shelgon
pokemon.blurb:
Inside SHELGONâs armor-like shell, cells
are in the midst of transformation
to create an entirely new body. This POKÃ©MONâs shell is extremely heavy,
making its movements sluggish.

pokemon.name: Salamence
pokemon.blurb:
SALAMENCE came about as a result of a
strong, long-held dream of growing
wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in
this POKÃ©MONâs cells, causing it to
sprout its magnificent wings.

pokemon.name: Beldum
pokemon.blurb:
Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic
force courses throughout BELDUMâs
body. This POKÃ©MON communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of
magnetism.

pokemon.name: Metang
pokemon.blurb:
When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG
is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are
joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically,
this POKÃ©MON generates strong
psychokinetic power.

pokemon.name: Metagross
pokemon.blurb:
METAGROSS has four brains in total.
Combined, the four brains can breeze
through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer.
This POKÃ©MON can float in the air by
tucking in its four legs.

pokemon.name: Regirock
pokemon.blurb:
REGIROCK was sealed away by people
long ago. If this POKÃ©MONâs body is
damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair
itself.

pokemon.name: Regice
pokemon.blurb:
REGICEâs body was made during an ice
age. The deep-frozen body canât be
melted, even by fire. This POKÃ©MON controls frigid air of
minus 328 degrees F.

pokemon.name: Registeel
pokemon.blurb:
REGISTEEL has a body that is harder
than any kind of metal.
Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKÃ©MON
eats.

pokemon.name: Latias
pokemon.blurb:
LATIAS is highly sensitive to the
emotions of people. If it senses any
hostility, this POKÃ©MON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries
shrilly to intimidate the foe.

pokemon.name: Latios
pokemon.blurb:
LATIOS has the ability to make its foe
see an image of what it has seen or
imagines in its head. This POKÃ©MON is intelligent and
understands human speech.

pokemon.name: Kyogre
pokemon.blurb:
KYOGRE has the power to create massive
rain clouds that cover the entire sky
and bring about torrential downpours. This POKÃ©MON saved people who were
suffering from droughts.

pokemon.name: Groudon
pokemon.blurb:
GROUDON has long been described in 
mythology as the POKÃ©MON that raised
lands and expanded continents. This POKÃ©MON took to sleep after a
cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.

pokemon.name: Rayquaza
pokemon.blurb:
RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions
of years in the earthâs ozone layer, 
never descending to the ground. This POKÃ©MON appears to feed on water
and particles in the atmosphere.

pokemon.name: Jirachi
pokemon.blurb:
A legend states that JIRACHI will make
true any wish that is written on notes
attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKÃ©MON senses danger, it will
fight without awakening.

pokemon.name: Deoxys-normal
pokemon.blurb:
An alien virus that fell to earth
on a meteor underwent a DNA
mutation to become this PokÃ©mon.

pokemon.name: Turtwig
pokemon.blurb:
Made from soil, the shell on its
back hardens when it drinks water.
It lives along lakes.

pokemon.name: Grotle
pokemon.blurb:
It lives along water in forests. In
the daytime, it leaves the forest
to sunbathe its treed shell.

pokemon.name: Torterra
pokemon.blurb:
Small PokÃ©mon occasionally gather
on its unmoving back to begin
building their nests.

pokemon.name: Chimchar
pokemon.blurb:
It agilely scales sheer cliffs to
live atop craggy mountains. Its
fire is put out when it sleeps.

pokemon.name: Monferno
pokemon.blurb:
To intimidate attackers, it
stretches the fire on its tail
to make itself appear bigger.

pokemon.name: Infernape
pokemon.blurb:
It uses a special kind of martial
arts involving all its limbs.
Its fire never goes out.

pokemon.name: Piplup
pokemon.blurb:
Because it is very proud, it hates
accepting food from people. Its
thick down guards it from cold.

pokemon.name: Prinplup
pokemon.blurb:
It lives alone, away from others.
Apparently, every one of them
believes it is the most important.

pokemon.name: Empoleon
pokemon.blurb:
The three horns that extend from
its beak attest to its power. The
leader has the biggest horns.

pokemon.name: Starly
pokemon.blurb:
They flock in great numbers.
Though small, they flap their
wings with great power.

pokemon.name: Staravia
pokemon.blurb:
It flies around forests and fields
in search of bug PokÃ©mon.
It stays within a huge flock.

pokemon.name: Staraptor
pokemon.blurb:
It has a savage nature. It will
courageously challenge foes that
are much larger.

pokemon.name: Bidoof
pokemon.blurb:
With nerves of steel, nothing can
perturb it. It is more agile and
active than it appears.

pokemon.name: Bibarel
pokemon.blurb:
It makes its nest by damming
streams with bark and mud. It is
known as an industrious worker.

pokemon.name: Kricketot
pokemon.blurb:
It shakes its head back to front,
causing its antennae to hit each
other and sound like a xylophone.

pokemon.name: Kricketune
pokemon.blurb:
It crosses its knifelike arms in
front of its chest when it cries.
It can compose melodies ad lib.

pokemon.name: Shinx
pokemon.blurb:
All of its fur dazzles if danger is
sensed. It flees while the foe is
momentarily blinded.

pokemon.name: Luxio
pokemon.blurb:
Its claws loose electricity with
enough amperage to cause fainting.
They live in small groups.

pokemon.name: Luxray
pokemon.blurb:
It has eyes that can see through
anything. It spots and captures
prey hiding behind objects.

pokemon.name: Budew
pokemon.blurb:
Over the winter, it closes its bud
and endures the cold. In spring,
the bud opens and releases pollen.

pokemon.name: Roserade
pokemon.blurb:
It attracts prey with a sweet
aroma, then downs it with
thorny whips hidden in its arms.

pokemon.name: Cranidos
pokemon.blurb:
It lived in jungles around 100
million years ago. Its skull is as
hard as iron.

pokemon.name: Rampardos
pokemon.blurb:
Its powerful head butt has enough
power to shatter even the most
durable things upon impact.

pokemon.name: Shieldon
pokemon.blurb:
A PokÃ©mon that lived in jungles
around 100 million years ago. Its
facial hide is extremely hard.

pokemon.name: Bastiodon
pokemon.blurb:
Any frontal attack is repulsed.
It is a docile PokÃ©mon that
feeds on grass and berries.

pokemon.name: Burmy
pokemon.blurb:
To shelter itself from cold, wintry
winds, it covers itself with a cloak
made of twigs and leaves.

pokemon.name: Wormadam-plant
pokemon.blurb:
When BURMY evolved, its cloak
became a part of this PokÃ©monâs
body. The cloak is never shed.

pokemon.name: Mothim
pokemon.blurb:
It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey
collected by Combee.

pokemon.name: Combee
pokemon.blurb:
A PokÃ©mon formed by three others.
It busily carries sweet floral
honey to VESPIQUEN.

pokemon.name: Vespiquen
pokemon.blurb:
Its abdomen is a honeycomb for
grubs. It raises its grubs on
honey collected by COMBEE.

pokemon.name: Pachirisu
pokemon.blurb:
It makes fur balls that crackle
with static electricity. It stores
them with berries in tree holes.

pokemon.name: Buizel
pokemon.blurb:
It has a flotation sac that is
like an inflatable collar. It floats
on water with its head out.

pokemon.name: Floatzel
pokemon.blurb:
It floats using its well-developed
flotation sac. It assists in the
rescues of drowning people.

pokemon.name: Cherubi
pokemon.blurb:
The small ball holds the nutrients
needed for evolution. Apparently,
it is very sweet and tasty.

pokemon.name: Cherrim
pokemon.blurb:
It blooms during times of strong
sunlight. It tries to make up for
everything it endured as a bud.

pokemon.name: Shellos
pokemon.blurb:
Its colors and shapes differ from
region to region. In the Sinnoh
region, two types are confirmed.

pokemon.name: Gastrodon
pokemon.blurb:
It has a pliable body without any
bones. If any part of its body is
torn off, it grows right back.

pokemon.name: Ambipom
pokemon.blurb:
To eat, it deftly shucks nuts
with its two tails. It rarely uses
its arms now.

pokemon.name: Drifloon
pokemon.blurb:
A PokÃ©mon formed by the spirits
of people and PokÃ©mon. It loves
damp, humid seasons.

pokemon.name: Drifblim
pokemon.blurb:
Itâs drowzy in daytime, but flies
off in the evening in big groups.
No one knows where they go.

pokemon.name: Buneary
pokemon.blurb:
It slams foes by sharply uncoiling
its rolled ears. It stings enough
to make a grown-up cry in pain.

pokemon.name: Lopunny
pokemon.blurb:
An extremely cautious PokÃ©mon.
It cloaks its body with its fluffy
ear fur when it senses danger.

pokemon.name: Mismagius
pokemon.blurb:
Its cries sound like incantations.
Those hearing it are tormented
by headaches and hallucinations.

pokemon.name: Honchkrow
pokemon.blurb:
Becoming active at night, it is
known to swarm with numerous
MURKROW in tow.

pokemon.name: Glameow
pokemon.blurb:
It claws if displeased and purrs
when affectionate. Its fickleness
is very popular among some.

pokemon.name: Purugly
pokemon.blurb:
It is a brazen brute that barges
its way into another PokÃ©monâs
nest and claims it as its own.

pokemon.name: Chingling
pokemon.blurb:
It emits cries by agitating an orb
at the back of its throat.
It moves with flouncing hops.

pokemon.name: Stunky
pokemon.blurb:
It protects itself by spraying a
noxious fluid from its rear. The
stench lingers for 24 hours.

pokemon.name: Skuntank
pokemon.blurb:
It sprays a vile-smelling fluid
from the tip of its tail to attack.
Its range is over 160 feet.

pokemon.name: Bronzor
pokemon.blurb:
Implements shaped like it were
discovered in ancient tombs. It is
unknown if they are related.

pokemon.name: Bronzong
pokemon.blurb:
One caused a news sensation when
it was dug up at a construction
site after a 2,000-year sleep.

pokemon.name: Bonsly
pokemon.blurb:
It looks as if it is always crying.
It is actually adjusting its bodyâs
fluid levels by eliminating excess.

pokemon.name: Mime-jr
pokemon.blurb:
It habitually mimics foes. Once
mimicked, the foe cannot take its
eyes off this PokÃ©mon.

pokemon.name: Happiny
pokemon.blurb:
It loves round white things.
It carries an egg-shaped rock in
imitation of CHANSEY.

pokemon.name: Chatot
pokemon.blurb:
It can learn and speak human
words. If they gather, they all
learn the same saying.

pokemon.name: Spiritomb
pokemon.blurb:
A PokÃ©mon that was formed by 108
spirits. It is bound to a fissure
in an odd keystone.

pokemon.name: Gible
pokemon.blurb:
It nests in small, horizontal holes
in cave walls. It pounces to catch
prey that stray too close.

pokemon.name: Gabite
pokemon.blurb:
There is a long-held belief that
medicine made from its scales will
heal even incurable illnesses.

pokemon.name: Garchomp
pokemon.blurb:
When it folds up its body and
extends its wings, it looks like a
jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

pokemon.name: Munchlax
pokemon.blurb:
It wolfs down its weight in food
once a day, swallowing food whole
with almost no chewing.

pokemon.name: Riolu
pokemon.blurb:
The aura that emanates from its
body intensifies to alert others
if it is afraid or sad.

pokemon.name: Lucario
pokemon.blurb:
It has the ability to sense the
auras of all things.
It understands human speech.

pokemon.name: Hippopotas
pokemon.blurb:
It lives in arid places. Instead
of perspiration, it expels grainy
sand from its body.

pokemon.name: Hippowdon
pokemon.blurb:
It blasts internally stored sand
from ports on its body to create
a towering twister for attack.

pokemon.name: Skorupi
pokemon.blurb:
It grips prey with its tail claws
and injects poison. It tenaciously
hangs on until the poison takes.

pokemon.name: Drapion
pokemon.blurb:
It has the power in its clawed
arms to make scrap of a car. The
tips of its claws release poison.

pokemon.name: Croagunk
pokemon.blurb:
Its cheeks hold poison sacs.
It tries to catch foes off guard
to jab them with toxic fingers.

pokemon.name: Toxicroak
pokemon.blurb:
Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin
so vile that even a scratch could
prove fatal.

pokemon.name: Carnivine
pokemon.blurb:
It attracts prey with its sweet-
smelling saliva, then chomps down.
It takes a whole day to eat prey.

pokemon.name: Finneon
pokemon.blurb:
The line running down its side can
store sunlight. It shines vividly at
night.

pokemon.name: Lumineon
pokemon.blurb:
It lives on the deep-sea floor.
It attracts prey by flashing the
patterns on its four tail fins.

pokemon.name: Mantyke
pokemon.blurb:
A friendly PokÃ©mon that captures
the subtle flows of seawater using
its two antennae.

pokemon.name: Snover
pokemon.blurb:
It lives on snowy mountains.
Having had little contact with
humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

pokemon.name: Abomasnow
pokemon.blurb:
It whips up blizzards in mountains
that are always buried in snow.
It is the abominable snowman.

pokemon.name: Weavile
pokemon.blurb:
They live in cold regions, forming
groups of four or five that hunt
prey with impressive coordination.

pokemon.name: Magnezone
pokemon.blurb:
It evolved from exposure to a
special magnetic field.
Three units generate magnetism.

pokemon.name: Lickilicky
pokemon.blurb:
It wraps things with its extensible
tongue. Getting too close to it
will leave you soaked with drool.

pokemon.name: Rhyperior
pokemon.blurb:
It puts rocks in holes in its palms
and uses its muscles to shoot them.
GEODUDE are shot at rare times.

pokemon.name: Tangrowth
pokemon.blurb:
It ensnares prey by extending
arms made of vines. Losing arms to
predators does not trouble it.

pokemon.name: Electivire
pokemon.blurb:
It pushes the tips of its two tails
against the foe, then lets loose
with over 20,000 volts of power.

pokemon.name: Magmortar
pokemon.blurb:
It blasts fireballs of over 3,600
degrees F from the ends of its
arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

pokemon.name: Togekiss
pokemon.blurb:
It will never appear where there
is strife. Its sightings have
become rare recently.

pokemon.name: Yanmega
pokemon.blurb:
By churning its wings, it creates
shock waves that inflict critical
internal injuries to foes.

pokemon.name: Leafeon
pokemon.blurb:
Just like a plant, it uses
photosynthesis. As a result, it is
always enveloped in clear air.

pokemon.name: Glaceon
pokemon.blurb:
As a protective technique, it can
completely freeze its fur to make
its hairs stand like needles.

pokemon.name: Gliscor
pokemon.blurb:
It observes prey while hanging
inverted from branches. When the
chance presents itself, it swoops!

pokemon.name: Mamoswine
pokemon.blurb:
Its impressive tusks are made of
ice. The population thinned when it
turned warm after the ice age.

pokemon.name: Porygon-z
pokemon.blurb:
Additional software was installed
to make it a better PokÃ©mon.
It began acting oddly, however.

pokemon.name: Gallade
pokemon.blurb:
A master of courtesy and
swordsmanship, it fights using
extending swords on its elbows.

pokemon.name: Probopass
pokemon.blurb:
It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses
using magnetic force.

pokemon.name: Dusknoir
pokemon.blurb:
The antenna on its head captures
radio waves from the world of spirits
that command it to take people there.

pokemon.name: Froslass
pokemon.blurb:
It freezes foes with an icy breath
nearly -60 degrees F. What seems
to be its body is actually hollow.

pokemon.name: Rotom
pokemon.blurb:
Its body is composed of plasma. It
is known to infiltrate electronic
devices and wreak havoc.

pokemon.name: Uxie
pokemon.blurb:
Known as âThe Being of Knowledge.â
It is said that it can wipe out the
memory of those who see its eyes.

pokemon.name: Mesprit
pokemon.blurb:
Known as âThe Being of Emotion.â
It taught humans the nobility of
sorrow, pain, and joy.

pokemon.name: Azelf
pokemon.blurb:
Known as âThe Being of Willpower.â
It sleeps at the bottom of a lake
to keep the world in balance.

pokemon.name: Dialga
pokemon.blurb:
It has the power to control time.
It appears in Sinnoh-region myths
as an ancient deity.

pokemon.name: Palkia
pokemon.blurb:
It has the ability to distort
space. It is described as a deity
in Sinnoh-region mythology.

pokemon.name: Heatran
pokemon.blurb:
It dwells in volcanic caves. It
digs in with its cross-shaped feet
to crawl on ceilings and walls.

pokemon.name: Regigigas
pokemon.blurb:
There is an enduring legend that
states this PokÃ©mon towed
continents with ropes.

pokemon.name: Giratina-altered
pokemon.blurb:
A PokÃ©mon that is said to live in a
world on the reverse side of ours.
It appears in an ancient cemetery.

pokemon.name: Cresselia
pokemon.blurb:
Shiny particles are released from
its wings like a veil. It is said
to represent the crescent moon.

pokemon.name: Phione
pokemon.blurb:
A PokÃ©mon that lives in warm seas.
It inflates the flotation sac on its
head to drift and search for food.

pokemon.name: Manaphy
pokemon.blurb:
Born on a cold seafloor, it
will swim great distances to
return to its birthplace.

pokemon.name: Darkrai
pokemon.blurb:
It can lull people to sleep and
make them dream. It is active
during nights of the new moon.

pokemon.name: Shaymin-land
pokemon.blurb:
It lives in flower patches and
avoids detection by curling up
to look like a flowering plant.

pokemon.name: Arceus
pokemon.blurb:
It is described in mythology as
the PokÃ©mon that shaped the
universe with its 1,000 arms.

pokemon.name: Victini
pokemon.blurb:
This PokÃ©mon brings victory. It is said
that Trainers with Victini always win,
regardless of the type of encounter.

pokemon.name: Snivy
pokemon.blurb:
It is very intelligent and calm.
Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes
its movements swifter.

pokemon.name: Servine
pokemon.blurb:
It moves along the ground as if sliding.
Its swift movements befuddle its foes,
and it then attacks with a vine whip.

pokemon.name: Serperior
pokemon.blurb:
It can stop its opponentsâ
movements with just a glare. It takes
in solar energy and boosts it internally.

pokemon.name: Tepig
pokemon.blurb:
It can deftly dodge its foeâs attacks
while shooting fireballs from its nose.
It roasts berries before it eats them.

pokemon.name: Pignite
pokemon.blurb:
When its internal fire flares up, its
movements grow sharper and faster.
When in trouble, it emits smoke.

pokemon.name: Emboar
pokemon.blurb:
It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves.
It grows a beard of fire.

pokemon.name: Oshawott
pokemon.blurb:
It fights using the scalchop on its
stomach. In response to an attack,
it retaliates immediately by slashing.

pokemon.name: Dewott
pokemon.blurb:
Strict training is how it learns its
flowing double-scalchop technique.

pokemon.name: Samurott
pokemon.blurb:
One swing of the sword incorporated in
its armor can fell an opponent. A simple
glare from one of them quiets everybody.

pokemon.name: Patrat
pokemon.blurb:
Using food stored in cheek pouches,
they can keep watch for days. They use
their tails to communicate with others.

pokemon.name: Watchog
pokemon.blurb:
When they see an enemy, their tails
stand high, and they spit the seeds of
berries stored in their cheek pouches.

pokemon.name: Lillipup
pokemon.blurb:
It faces strong opponents with great
courage. But, when at a disadvantage in
a fight, this intelligent PokÃ©mon flees.

pokemon.name: Herdier
pokemon.blurb:
This very loyal PokÃ©mon
helps Trainers, and it also
takes care of other PokÃ©mon.

pokemon.name: Stoutland
pokemon.blurb:
It rescues people stranded by
blizzards in the mountains. Its
shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

pokemon.name: Purrloin
pokemon.blurb:
They steal from people for fun, but their
victims canât help but forgive them.
Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

pokemon.name: Liepard
pokemon.blurb:
These PokÃ©mon vanish and appear
unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn
to their beautiful form and fur.

pokemon.name: Pansage
pokemon.blurb:
This PokÃ©mon dwells deep in the forest.
Eating a leaf from its head whisks
weariness away as if by magic.

pokemon.name: Simisage
pokemon.blurb:
Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its
barbed tail around wildly. The leaf
growing on its head is very bitter.

pokemon.name: Pansear
pokemon.blurb:
When it is angered, the temperature
of its head tuft reaches 600Â° F.
It uses its tuft to roast berries.

pokemon.name: Simisear
pokemon.blurb:
It loves sweets because they become
energy for the fire burning inside
its body.

pokemon.name: Panpour
pokemon.blurb:
The water stored inside the tuft on
its head is full of nutrients. Plants
that receive its water grow large.

pokemon.name: Simipour
pokemon.blurb:
The tuft on its head holds water. When
the level runs low, it replenishes the
tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

pokemon.name: Munna
pokemon.blurb:
Munna always float in the air. People
whose dreams are eaten by them
forget what the dreams had been about.

pokemon.name: Musharna
pokemon.blurb:
The mist emanating from their foreheads
is packed with the dreams of people
and PokÃ©mon.

pokemon.name: Pidove
pokemon.blurb:
Each follows its Trainerâs orders as
best it can, but they sometimes fail to
understand complicated commands.

pokemon.name: Tranquill
pokemon.blurb:
It can return to its Trainerâs location
regardless of the distance
separating them.

pokemon.name: Unfezant
pokemon.blurb:
Males swing their head plumage to
threaten opponents. The femalesâ flying
abilities surpass those of the males.

pokemon.name: Blitzle
pokemon.blurb:
Its mane shines when it discharges
electricity. They use their flashing
manes to communicate with one another.

pokemon.name: Zebstrika
pokemon.blurb:
They have lightning-like movements.
When Zebstrika run at full speed,
the sound of thunder reverberates.

pokemon.name: Roggenrola
pokemon.blurb:
Its ear is hexagonal in shape.
Compressed underground,
its body is as hard as steel.

pokemon.name: Boldore
pokemon.blurb:
When it overflows with power,
the orange crystal on its body glows.
It looks for underground water in caves.

pokemon.name: Gigalith
pokemon.blurb:
Compressing the energy from its
internal core lets it fire off an attack
capable of blowing away a mountain.

pokemon.name: Woobat
pokemon.blurb:
Its habitat is dark forests and caves.
It emits ultrasonic waves from its
nose to learn about its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Swoobat
pokemon.blurb:
It emits sound waves of various
frequencies from its nose, including
some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

pokemon.name: Drilbur
pokemon.blurb:
It can dig through the ground
at a speed of 30 mph. It could give
a car running aboveground a good race.

pokemon.name: Excadrill
pokemon.blurb:
It can help in tunnel construction.
Its drill has evolved into steel strong
enough to bore through iron plates.

pokemon.name: Audino
pokemon.blurb:
It touches others with the feelers on
its ears, using the sound of their
heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

pokemon.name: Timburr
pokemon.blurb:
It fights by swinging a piece of lumber
around. It is close to evolving when it
can handle the lumber without difficulty.

pokemon.name: Gurdurr
pokemon.blurb:
This PokÃ©mon is so muscular and strongly
built that even a group of wrestlers
